      • getDomain

        public NodeSpecification getDomain()
        Return the domain name of this inq server. The domain name is read from the server's properties file which, in turn, is specified by the -properties {file} command line option. The domain is the value of the inq.server.domain property.
        Returns:
        the domain as a node specification or null if there is no domain specified

      • setDomain

        public void setDomain()

      • setDomain

        public void setDomain(Any d)
        Sets the domain of this server. If the supplied argument is null then we look for the property inq.server.domain.

        If an argument is given then the domain is set to this value but this can only be performed once.
